The police Search and Rescue Team on Sunday recovered three bodies from Levubu and one from Giyani respectively.The three, a woman and two males, were traveling in a vehicle on Saturday when it crashed into the Levubu river during which all occupants have drowned. Their bodies were recovered on Sunday.In Giyani, the body of Tebogo Ngonyama (19) whom it&#8217;s also alleged to be the victim of an armed robbery that was reported at Giyani police station, was recovered on Sunday from the Ritavi river by the same Search and Rescue team.As rains persist in some parts of our province, SAPS urged members of the community to exercise caution and to practice #WaterSafety when crossing rivers and only cross at relevant places when it is safe to do so.-TNA Reporter